  "body": "## Problem \r\n\r\nOpening the new Activity Center with at least one notification causes an infinite number of calls to fetch the first page of notifications.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nFetch the first page once.\r\n\r\n#### Root cause\r\n\r\nWhen notifications are fetched from status-go, the namespace `status-im.data-store.activities/<-rpc` augments the notifications with a random color in the set `quo.design-system.colors/chat-colors`. This is no longer needed and the visual appearance of a notification shouldn't be a responsibility of the data store in the first place.\r\n\r\nBecause notifications are given random color strings, the `quo.react/effect!` dependencies' vector equality check always gives false.\r\n\r\n#### Solution\r\n\r\nRemove the random color key from `status-im.data-store.activities/<-rpc`.\r\n\r\n",
